snippet.textDisplay: It's a visual masterpiece that deserves to applauded for the stunning images and vibrant atmosphere that was so masterfully created but this is the first song from this season that I didn't like. The song itself is disjointed and too many parts have been added that clash instead of seamlessly harmonizing together. I liked Umar Butt's part but Faris wasn't great, the sisters' part was unnecessary and the kid's portion was completely incompatible with the song and made it a jumbled mess. All the songs of this season have successfully managed to strike a beautiful balance between incredible vocals and stunning visuals except this one. Also, I am part Punjabi myself but there's been enough Punjabi songs in this season. Kindly create more Urdu songs and songs from other Pakistani languages as well.
snippet.textOriginal: It's a visual masterpiece that deserves to applauded for the stunning images and vibrant atmosphere that was so masterfully created but this is the first song from this season that I didn't like.
